bmo: Here’s a concise report on the frontend repository.

High-level overview
- Purpose: JavaScript monorepo for ngrok’s frontend web apps and shared code.
- Stack: React 19 + React Router 7, TypeScript 5, Tailwind CSS 4, Vitest, Turborepo, pnpm 10.
- Package manager: pnpm@10.23.0 with strict pinning and a shared catalog.
- Monorepo management: Turborepo with remote caching enabled (turborepo.corp.ngrok.com).
- Formatting/linting: Biome.
- Testing: Vitest (+ happy-dom), some Playwright setup via internal action.

Structure
- apps/: www, blog, dashboard, ngrok-ai (all React Router apps).
  - www: public site (Vercel deploys).
  - blog: MDX-based blog (Vercel deploys; auto-format workflow for MDX).
  - dashboard: primary product UI; uses Tanstack Query/Form, connects to a Go backend via Connect RPC; deployed as a container (GitHub package registry, then referenced from ngrok monorepo).
  - ngrok-ai: ngrok.ai site (Vercel deploys).
- packages/: ui, test-utils, dep-ext, common, proto-js-utils, hooks, icons, proto-js.
  - common: shared, unopinionated helpers (build regenerates exports map).
  - proto-js: generated protocol buffer types from ngrok monorepo; updated via scripts/workflow.
- config/: shared tsconfig and tsup configs.
- scripts/: utility scripts (e.g., clean-node-modules.js).
- .github/workflows/: CI/CD (see below).

Key conventions and tooling
- Strict dependency pinning (no ^/~). Shared dependencies referenced with catalog: protocol (centralized in pnpm-workspace.yaml).
- Workspace dependency policy: internal deps via workspace:*; for packages, external deps generally in devDependencies/peerDependencies; prefer catalog for shared libs.
- Formatting: Biome with tabs (width 2 spaces), double quotes; import organization automated.
- TypeScript: strict mode; shared configs via @cfg/tsconfig.
- Control flow (AGENT.md): always use braces, avoid any.

Build and dev
- Turbo tasks: build, build-@pkg (shared packages), start, test, typecheck, fmt, clean, update:protos.
- Remote cache enabled; many tasks depend on building shared packages first (^build-@pkg).
- Key root scripts: start/build/test/typecheck/fmt across the workspace via turbo.

Dependency management
- pnpm-workspace.yaml defines:
  - packages: apps/*, config/*, packages/*.
  - minimumReleaseAge: 12 hours for new package versions (supply chain safety).
  - catalog: centralized exact versions for React, Vite, TypeScript, etc.
- Root package.json enforces some overrides (e.g., @mjackson/node-fetch-server → @remix-run/node-fetch-server).

CI/CD
- Vibe Check workflow: install, fmt/lint, proto-gen check (ensures no diffs), setup Playwright, then build/typecheck/test via turbo.
- App deployments:
  - www/blog/ngrok-ai: Vercel (preview + production). Supports skipping preview by label or PR description sentinel.
  - dashboard: builds a container on merge to main, publishes to GitHub registry, then bumps a SHA in ngrok monorepo via Buildkite; deployable via internal pipelines.
- Blog-specific automation: auto-format MDX in PRs.

Security and reliability practices
- Strict pinned versions + shared catalog.
- minimumReleaseAge: blocks packages <12 hours old (thwarts newly published malicious releases).
- Remote turbo cache for reproducible builds.
- Proto sync check in CI fails on uncommitted generation diffs.

Environment and configuration
- direnv + .envrc for automated tool setup (fnm + Node + pnpm).
- Dashboard uses Vite mode-aware env system with NGROK_ENV (lan/dev/stage; production for builds). Key env var: VITE_NGROK_APP_API_URL.
- Ports:
  - dashboard: 3000 by README (app note says default mode stage).
  - blog: 8106.
  - ngrok-ai/www: 5173.

Notable docs vs config mismatches to resolve
- Node version:
  - README/AGENT.md mention Node.js 22.
  - Root package.json engines requires node ^24.0.0 and packageManager is pnpm@10.23.0.
  - .nvmrc exists (CI uses it) and likely pins Node 24; align docs to Node 24.
- Tailwind/Vitest versions:
  - README says Tailwind CSS 4, Vitest 3.
  - Catalog pins tailwindcss 4.1.17 (OK), but root devDependency lists vitest 4.0.17 (docs say 3). Update docs or dependency as intended.
- Packages list in README vs repo:
  - README mentions shared; repo has common (and additional ui, test-utils, proto-js-utils). Update README/AGENT to reflect current packages.

Quick commands (from root)
- Install + bootstrap: pnpm install -w; pnpm -w run bootstrap.
- Build: pnpm -w run build.
- Dev (all apps): pnpm -w run start; or filter with -F @app/<name>.
- Test: pnpm -w run test (and test:watch).
- Typecheck: pnpm -w run typecheck.
- Format/lint: pnpm -w run fmt; check: pnpm -w run fmt:check.
- Update protos: pnpm -w run gen:proto.

Overall assessment
- Well-structured monorepo with strong dependency hygiene, clear CI safeguards, and well-documented app/deployment flows.
- Minor documentation drift (Node version, Vitest version, package names) should be corrected to prevent confusion.
- Dashboard deployment pipeline is robust and integrated with the main ngrok monorepo; other apps use straightforward Vercel workflows.
